item.title: When we should use LinkedHashMap?
item.description: LinkedHashMap can be used to maintain insertion order, on which keys are inserted into Map or it can also be used to maintain an access order, on which keys are accessed. This provides LinkedHashMap an edge over HashMap without compromising too much performance. Which is better LinkedHashMap or HashMap?
